Nasarawa State chapter of N-Power volunteers have expressed support for the continuation of the programme and other social investment programmes by the Federal Government across the country. N-Power coordinator in the state, Salisu Abdusalam said since its introduction, the scheme has addressed the problem of unemployment in education, agriculture and health sectors of the economy. Abdusalam who spoke at an event organized by the volunteers to express support for the programme also urged the federal government to find a means of absorbing employees under the scheme into the civil service. “We suggest that a well synergized plan between the federal government and state government to integrate the trained and equipped young graduates into a workable system where they can put into practice skills they have acquired,” he said.